            <p>In-person consultations are available at the Woodbine Avenue office — no long drive across the city. Miao He is familiar with the Markham community, the York Region court system, and the specific legal issues that arise most often among local Chinese-Canadian families.</p>
            <p>Marriage contracts are increasingly common in Markham, particularly where parents have contributed to a down payment or where family business assets need protection. Miao He drafts marriage contracts in both Chinese and English and ensures they meet Ontario court standards for enforceability.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Frequently Asked Question</h2>
            <p class="faq-q">My parents paid the down payment on our Markham home. Can my spouse claim half of it in a divorce?</p>
            <p>It depends on documentation and how title is registered. If the gift can be proven to be made to you alone — not to both spouses — it may be excluded from the Equalization calculation. Miao He has handled many Markham cases involving parental contributions and can assess your situation directly.</p>
